
[1]appall

   APPALL', v.t. [L. palleo, to become pale. See Pale.]

   1. To depress or discourage with fear; to impress with fear, in such a
   manner that the mind shrinks, or loses its firmness; as, the sight
   appalled the stoutest heart.

   2. To reduce, allay or destroy; as, to appall thirst. [Unusual.]

                APPALL', v.i. To grow faint; to be dismayed.
